column13: A method and an apparatus for enabling the aseptic transfer of a fluid which is in one sterile container to another sterile container are disclosed. Each container is provided with a connector enclosing a cavity in communication with the sterile container. The connector is made of a material that melts and flows at a predetermined temperature and has an insert that is resistant to such temperature conditions. In use, the two connectors are held together and subjected to heat and pressure so that contacting portions of the connectors melt and flow away to form a communicating opening between the connectors, while maintaining sterile and closed all other regions of the connectors.

column12: Apparatus for and method of supporting a crucible for EFG growth of sapphire
column13: A crucible for containing a melt and die for EFG growth of sapphire is supported by a pyrolytic graphite crucible support plate having the C axis of the pyrolytic graphite perpendicular to the bottom of the crucible which is supported by the plate. This thermally insulates the crucible from the pedestal which supports the support plate.

column13: The invention relates to a hula seal with preferential cooling. An annular seal (62) for use between coupled combustor components includes a segmented annular solid edge portion and a plurality of alternating spring fingers (66, 68, 72) and slots (70) extending from the solid edge portion and arranged about a circumference of the solid edge portion, wherein one or more of the plurality of spring fingers or one or more of the plurality of straight and angled slots have non-uniform width dimensions. A gas turbine combustor assembly and a method of preferentially cooling a region in a turbine combustor are also provided.
